>>REGINA: Because you said,
OK, I've got the school,

00:31:17.110 --> 00:31:21.140 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to start now, I want
to make $30,000 from this.

00:31:21.140 --> 00:31:21.940 align:middle line:90%
>>SIMON: Yeah.

00:31:21.940 --> 00:31:26.830 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And so you put it in
motion, boom, bingo, bada-bing,

00:31:26.830 --> 00:31:29.390 align:middle line:90%
you're making, you made $30,000.

00:31:29.390 --> 00:31:31.120 align:middle line:84%
But you tell the rest
the story for those

00:31:31.120 --> 00:31:32.260 align:middle line:90%
that haven't heard this.

00:31:32.260 --> 00:31:33.760 align:middle line:84%
>>SIMON: Well, the
rest of the story

00:31:33.760 --> 00:31:35.620 align:middle line:84%
is, when I reached
that goal, my tips

00:31:35.620 --> 00:31:40.540 align:middle line:84%
and tricks and my predictive
technique stopped,

00:31:40.540 --> 00:31:41.870 align:middle line:90%
kind of stopped working.

00:31:41.870 --> 00:31:43.660 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So let's talk about
that other factor at work.

00:31:43.660 --> 00:31:45.493 align:middle line:84%
>>SIMON: Yeah, this is
the spiritual factor.

00:31:45.493 --> 00:31:49.330 align:middle line:84%
Are you spiritually
aligned to take advantage,

00:31:49.330 --> 00:31:51.010 align:middle line:90%
to profit from this?

00:31:51.010 --> 00:31:54.460 align:middle line:84%
And that was with
my sports, that

00:31:54.460 --> 00:31:57.010 align:middle line:84%
was sort of the end
of my sports wagering.

00:31:57.010 --> 00:32:00.770 align:middle line:84%
Because it was leading me
down, it's a lot of work.

00:32:00.770 --> 00:32:03.820 align:middle line:84%
You know this, Regina, from,
you've been in this world

00:32:03.820 --> 00:32:06.700 align:middle line:84%
where you're watching 10
games at the same time,

00:32:06.700 --> 00:32:07.728 align:middle line:90%
you're doing charts.

00:32:07.728 --> 00:32:09.520 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I remember
that from my NBC days,

00:32:09.520 --> 00:32:09.990 align:middle line:84%
just trying to watch
all these games.

00:32:09.990 --> 00:32:11.140 align:middle line:90%
>>SIMON: It's crazy.

00:32:11.140 --> 00:32:12.770 align:middle line:90%
12 hours a day.

00:32:12.770 --> 00:32:14.590 align:middle line:84%
And so that's how
you earn your living.

00:32:14.590 --> 00:32:17.420 align:middle line:84%
And I reached a fork in
the road, I said, look,

00:32:17.420 --> 00:32:20.055 align:middle line:84%
I can earn a living doing this,
but I won't be able to teach,

00:32:20.055 --> 00:32:21.430 align:middle line:84%
I won't be able
to write books, I

00:32:21.430 --> 00:32:22.090 align:middle line:90%
won't be able to do the stuff.

00:32:22.090 --> 00:32:23.140 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Do your Dharma.

00:32:23.140 --> 00:32:24.820 align:middle line:90%
>>SIMON: Do my Dharma.

00:32:24.820 --> 00:32:26.920 align:middle line:84%
And it was clear that
this wasn't the road.

00:32:26.920 --> 00:32:30.970 align:middle line:84%
It was fun, it was awesome,
I still have fond memories,

00:32:30.970 --> 00:32:32.090 align:middle line:90%
but that was it.

00:32:32.090 --> 00:32:35.410 align:middle line:84%
And so my Dharma was, and
it was painful, by the way.

00:32:35.410 --> 00:32:36.370 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Mm-hmm.

00:32:36.370 --> 00:32:39.580 align:middle line:84%
>>SIMON: To have a
parlay where I predict 12

00:32:39.580 --> 00:32:41.920 align:middle line:84%
out of 13 teams right
and just the last team

00:32:41.920 --> 00:32:44.920 align:middle line:84%
loses by one point, and
you go, oh, somebody's

00:32:44.920 --> 00:32:47.530 align:middle line:90%
trying to tell me something.

00:32:47.530 --> 00:32:50.440 align:middle line:84%
And so now I've moved into doing
my Dharma, which is sharing,

00:32:50.440 --> 00:32:51.890 align:middle line:90%
researching other techniques.

00:32:51.890 --> 00:32:53.920 align:middle line:84%
So the lucky times
does not require

00:32:53.920 --> 00:32:57.105 align:middle line:84%
the same kind of sort of
spiritual alignment and faith.

00:32:57.105 --> 00:32:58.480 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But what
happens if you

00:32:58.480 --> 00:33:00.620 align:middle line:84%
get into a mindset of
greed, and you say,

00:33:00.620 --> 00:33:02.590 align:middle line:84%
OK, I'm doing these
slots every day.

00:33:02.590 --> 00:33:04.750 align:middle line:84%
Every lucky time,
I'm on it, man.

00:33:04.750 --> 00:33:07.100 align:middle line:84%
>>SIMON: Slots are designed
to take your money.

00:33:07.100 --> 00:33:12.853 align:middle line:84%
So with slots, if you break
even, even even, you're doing.

00:33:12.853 --> 00:33:14.020 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You're going well.

00:33:14.020 --> 00:33:14.350 align:middle line:90%
>>SIMON: You're doing well.

00:33:14.350 --> 00:33:16.270 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But most people
aren't going to see it that way.

00:33:16.270 --> 00:33:16.470 align:middle line:90%
>>SIMON: Right.

00:33:16.470 --> 00:33:17.870 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: They're going
to want to make money.

00:33:17.870 --> 00:33:18.670 align:middle line:90%
>>SIMON: Right.

00:33:18.670 --> 00:33:20.320 align:middle line:84%
So don't play slots
to make money.

00:33:20.320 --> 00:33:21.160 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK, good, thank you.

00:33:21.160 --> 00:33:22.540 align:middle line:84%
>>SIMON: I used
slot to test this.

00:33:22.540 --> 00:33:23.080 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:33:23.080 --> 00:33:25.480 align:middle line:84%
>>SIMON: To show you that
even a system that's rigged

00:33:25.480 --> 00:33:27.732 align:middle line:84%
to take your money,
you can beat it

00:33:27.732 --> 00:33:28.940 align:middle line:90%
for a certain amount of time.

00:33:28.940 --> 00:33:30.273 align:middle line:90%
But it's like swimming upstream.

00:33:30.273 --> 00:33:32.110 align:middle line:84%
You're going to get
tired after a while.

00:33:32.110 --> 00:33:33.140 align:middle line:90%
Use these techniques.

00:33:33.140 --> 00:33:34.250 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So this is
just a proof of concept.

00:33:34.250 --> 00:33:35.625 align:middle line:84%
>>SIMON: It's a
proof of concept.

00:33:35.625 --> 00:33:38.020 align:middle line:84%
Now if you love playing
slots and you do it anyway,

00:33:38.020 --> 00:33:39.370 align:middle line:90%
well, go for it.

00:33:39.370 --> 00:33:40.630 align:middle line:90%
Do your thing.

00:33:40.630 --> 00:33:43.710 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there's some people
in Vegas, ching-ching-ching.

00:33:43.710 --> 00:33:45.460 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But that's
what they love doing.

00:33:45.460 --> 00:33:48.040 align:middle line:84%
>>SIMON: And you go back eight
hours later, they're there.

00:33:48.040 --> 00:33:49.250 align:middle line:90%
Ding-ding-ding-ding.

00:33:49.250 --> 00:33:54.490 align:middle line:84%
So OK, use those times
to bet a little bigger

00:33:54.490 --> 00:33:55.445 align:middle line:90%
during those times.

00:33:55.445 --> 00:33:56.245 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:33:56.245 --> 00:33:57.590 align:middle line:90%
Go to the quarter machine.

00:33:57.590 --> 00:33:58.450 align:middle line:90%
>>SIMON: Go to the.

00:33:58.450 --> 00:34:00.450 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Instead of the
dime machine or nickel.

00:34:00.450 --> 00:34:03.080 align:middle line:84%
>>SIMON: Oh, no, I
played minimum $2 a ring.

00:34:03.080 --> 00:34:04.990 align:middle line:84%
I don't have time
for quarter machine.

00:34:04.990 --> 00:34:08.110 align:middle line:84%
But that's why I also
lose money sometime.

00:34:08.110 --> 00:34:10.600 align:middle line:84%
No, but overall,
I'm in the black.

00:34:10.600 --> 00:34:12.429 align:middle line:84%
Even with slots, I've
done pretty well.

00:34:12.429 --> 00:34:14.139 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I haven't
made a fortune,

00:34:14.139 --> 00:34:15.880 align:middle line:84%
but I've made a few
hundred bucks here,

00:34:15.880 --> 00:34:19.389 align:middle line:84%
a few hundred bucks there to
show that, hey, this works.

00:34:19.389 --> 00:34:22.550 align:middle line:84%
But use this to do the
things that you do.

00:34:22.550 --> 00:34:26.510 align:middle line:84%
If you're a stock investor, if
you are, I don't know, I mean,

00:34:26.510 --> 00:34:27.800 align:middle line:90%
if you are.

00:34:27.800 --> 00:34:28.580 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Like we
said, if you want

00:34:28.580 --> 00:34:30.500 align:middle line:84%
to just have an important
talk with somebody.

00:34:30.500 --> 00:34:31.370 align:middle line:90%
>>SIMON: Exactly.

00:34:31.370 --> 00:34:33.203 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Have the luck
energy on your side.

00:34:33.203 --> 00:34:35.130 align:middle line:84%
>>SIMON: We all did a
little sprinkle of luck.

00:34:35.130 --> 00:34:36.530 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, that's
why I wanted to talk about

00:34:36.530 --> 00:34:38.780 align:middle line:84%
this right now, because there
are many ways in which people

00:34:38.780 --> 00:34:40.909 align:middle line:84%
are praying for any kind
of good luck right now.

00:34:40.909 --> 00:34:44.254 align:middle line:84%
And you're just loading it
a little bit in their favor.

00:34:44.254 --> 00:34:47.300 align:middle line:84%
>>SIMON: And we
do, we can access

00:34:47.300 --> 00:34:50.179 align:middle line:84%
the rhythms of the universe,
the rhythms of the cosmos

00:34:50.179 --> 00:34:57.139 align:middle line:84%
to kind of, it's like birds
when they catch a thermal,

00:34:57.139 --> 00:34:58.670 align:middle line:84%
you don't need to
flap your wings.

00:34:58.670 --> 00:35:00.980 align:middle line:90%
You're just ahh.

00:35:00.980 --> 00:35:03.352 align:middle line:84%
And these lucky times
are like little thermals.

00:35:03.352 --> 00:35:04.560 align:middle line:90%
They give you a little boost.

00:35:04.560 --> 00:35:05.360 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:35:05.360 --> 00:35:07.070 align:middle line:90%
>>SIMON: Right?

00:35:07.070 --> 00:35:10.080 align:middle line:84%
And knowing where
they are, you decide

00:35:10.080 --> 00:35:11.330 align:middle line:90%
what you want to do with them.

00:35:11.330 --> 00:35:13.460 align:middle line:84%
My job is to show you when
it's going to be for you.

00:35:13.460 --> 00:35:13.780 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:35:13.780 --> 00:35:15.200 align:middle line:90%
No, that makes perfect sense.

00:35:15.200 --> 00:35:17.870 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, if we
were all perfectly

00:35:17.870 --> 00:35:19.553 align:middle line:84%
attuned with our
perfect tuning forks,

00:35:19.553 --> 00:35:20.720 align:middle line:90%
we would feel these moments.

00:35:20.720 --> 00:35:21.500 align:middle line:90%
>>SIMON: We don't need it, yeah.

00:35:21.500 --> 00:35:22.750 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: We wouldn't need it.

00:35:22.750 --> 00:35:25.820 align:middle line:84%
And there are people who are
that in touch with themselves.

00:35:25.820 --> 00:35:28.400 align:middle line:84%
They feel when there's
wind under their wings.

00:35:28.400 --> 00:35:29.810 align:middle line:90%
But not most people.

00:35:29.810 --> 00:35:32.550 align:middle line:84%
There's too much noise, too
much fear, just too much.

00:35:32.550 --> 00:35:34.550 align:middle line:84%
>>SIMON: I think almost
everyone has had moments

00:35:34.550 --> 00:35:38.660 align:middle line:84%
where you're like, I had a
dream this is going to happen,

00:35:38.660 --> 00:35:40.970 align:middle line:84%
or I have a feeling
this is going to happen,

00:35:40.970 --> 00:35:42.440 align:middle line:90%
and it happens.

00:35:42.440 --> 00:35:46.940 align:middle line:84%
But that tends to be
the, that's not the norm.

00:35:46.940 --> 00:35:48.155 align:middle line:90%
That's the anomaly.

00:35:48.155 --> 00:35:50.030 align:middle line:84%
What I want to do, is
give you the lucky time

00:35:50.030 --> 00:35:51.470 align:middle line:90%
so that becomes the norm.

00:35:51.470 --> 00:35:52.460 align:middle line:90%
Where you plug in.

00:35:52.460 --> 00:35:52.700 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:35:52.700 --> 00:35:53.780 align:middle line:84%
>>SIMON: And you know
what's going to happen

00:35:53.780 --> 00:35:55.905 align:middle line:84%
and you know you're going
to get a good result more

00:35:55.905 --> 00:35:56.705 align:middle line:90%
often than not.

00:35:56.705 --> 00:35:58.580 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Maybe I need
to look at my unlucky,

00:35:58.580 --> 00:36:00.292 align:middle line:84%
you were just
speaking those dreams,

00:36:00.292 --> 00:36:02.250 align:middle line:84%
I have these dreams, some
dreams yesterday that

00:36:02.250 --> 00:36:04.590 align:middle line:84%
were really interesting,
followed by right

00:36:04.590 --> 00:36:07.530 align:middle line:84%
after I woke up, wrote a couple
things down on the computer,

00:36:07.530 --> 00:36:09.750 align:middle line:84%
then closed my
computer, I was done.

00:36:09.750 --> 00:36:13.170 align:middle line:84%
After I closed the computer for
the first time in my awareness,

00:36:13.170 --> 00:36:15.330 align:middle line:84%
that computer started
playing video.

00:36:15.330 --> 00:36:17.450 align:middle line:84%
But it wasn't a
video, it was an ad.

00:36:17.450 --> 00:36:20.670 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, the words that came
out of my closed computer

00:36:20.670 --> 00:36:24.010 align:middle line:84%
were, accidents happen,
but we're here to help you.

00:36:24.010 --> 00:36:24.810 align:middle line:90%
>>SIMON: Wow.

00:36:24.810 --> 00:36:25.530 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Turns
out I think it was

00:36:25.530 --> 00:36:27.140 align:middle line:90%
an All State ad or something.

00:36:27.140 --> 00:36:29.520 align:middle line:84%
>>SIMON: Mars Saturn are
squared right now, yeah.

00:36:29.520 --> 00:36:31.350 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Oh, man,
was I careful.

00:36:31.350 --> 00:36:33.400 align:middle line:84%
I drove in some
alleys yesterday just

00:36:33.400 --> 00:36:34.650 align:middle line:90%
to kind of get off the street.

00:36:34.650 --> 00:36:36.510 align:middle line:84%
And then I thought, oh no,
you'll surprise someone

00:36:36.510 --> 00:36:38.010 align:middle line:90%
when you come out of the alley.

00:36:38.010 --> 00:36:41.990 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it really kind
of put me on my toes.

00:36:41.990 --> 00:36:44.940 align:middle line:84%
>>SIMON: And that is, well,
it's right now in the sky,

00:36:44.940 --> 00:36:46.350 align:middle line:84%
Mars and Saturn
are square, which

00:36:46.350 --> 00:36:47.280 align:middle line:90%
is an accident combination.

00:36:47.280 --> 00:36:48.080 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh!

00:36:48.080 --> 00:36:50.530 align:middle line:84%
>>SIMON: So, now it's
applicable to everyone.

00:36:50.530 --> 00:36:51.330 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Everyone.

00:36:51.330 --> 00:36:53.400 align:middle line:84%
>>SIMON: But it
means if you're angry

00:36:53.400 --> 00:36:56.640 align:middle line:84%
or if you have, you're thinking
about stuff and you're driving,

00:36:56.640 --> 00:36:58.740 align:middle line:90%
you're more likely to mess up.

00:36:58.740 --> 00:37:01.470 align:middle line:84%
So all it means is,
just pay more attention.

00:37:01.470 --> 00:37:02.270 align:middle line:90%
You'll be fine.

00:37:02.270 --> 00:37:02.640 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:37:02.640 --> 00:37:04.480 align:middle line:84%
Well, I'm going to bring up
another little dream then.

00:37:04.480 --> 00:37:06.270 align:middle line:84%
OK, this was the dream
that just preceded it,

00:37:06.270 --> 00:37:07.230 align:middle line:90%
which was interesting.

00:37:07.230 --> 00:37:08.880 align:middle line:84%
And I won't go into
details, but it

00:37:08.880 --> 00:37:11.580 align:middle line:84%
was kind of how I was
doing in a spiritual study.

00:37:11.580 --> 00:37:14.460 align:middle line:84%
And it turned into a graph
chart and showing all this stuff

00:37:14.460 --> 00:37:16.390 align:middle line:84%
up here, you're doing
great and everything.

00:37:16.390 --> 00:37:18.990 align:middle line:84%
And then it had a little
white box here that said,

00:37:18.990 --> 00:37:21.750 align:middle line:90%
naivete, naivete.

00:37:21.750 --> 00:37:24.900 align:middle line:84%
And I thought like,
that was something,

00:37:24.900 --> 00:37:26.212 align:middle line:90%
something was going on there.

00:37:26.212 --> 00:37:28.420 align:middle line:84%
So I waited until this
morning and I meditated on it.

00:37:28.420 --> 00:37:29.970 align:middle line:84%
And I bring this
up for a reason.

00:37:29.970 --> 00:37:33.060 align:middle line:84%
Right now is the time that
people are feeling angry,

00:37:33.060 --> 00:37:35.470 align:middle line:84%
they're shutting down,
they're mistrustful.

00:37:35.470 --> 00:37:37.530 align:middle line:84%
And the message that
came through when I said,

00:37:37.530 --> 00:37:40.430 align:middle line:84%
what did that mean,
it said naivete

00:37:40.430 --> 00:37:42.820 align:middle line:90%
is in service of the soul.

00:37:42.820 --> 00:37:45.150 align:middle line:84%
It leaves you open to
what we're talking about,

00:37:45.150 --> 00:37:47.880 align:middle line:84%
these updrafts, the
messaging from the soul,

00:37:47.880 --> 00:37:51.160 align:middle line:84%
for new information to
come in without resistance.

00:37:51.160 --> 00:37:53.482 align:middle line:84%
And if you get burned here
and there because maybe you

00:37:53.482 --> 00:37:55.440 align:middle line:84%
bought something that
you weren't shrewd enough

00:37:55.440 --> 00:37:57.600 align:middle line:90%
to detect, it happens.

00:37:57.600 --> 00:37:59.100 align:middle line:90%
It happens to all of us.

00:37:59.100 --> 00:38:02.160 align:middle line:84%
But this notion of
staying open to life.

00:38:02.160 --> 00:38:04.130 align:middle line:90%
>>SIMON: Yeah.

00:38:04.130 --> 00:38:05.570 align:middle line:90%
It's also called surrender.

00:38:05.570 --> 00:38:06.370 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:38:06.370 --> 00:38:08.500 align:middle line:84%
>>SIMON: And surrender
doesn't mean giving up.

00:38:08.500 --> 00:38:12.610 align:middle line:84%
It means knowing,
it means opening

00:38:12.610 --> 00:38:16.880 align:middle line:84%
your armor a little bit, so that
you can let in, let people in.

00:38:16.880 --> 00:38:18.650 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Vulnerable,
be vulnerable.

00:38:18.650 --> 00:38:19.550 align:middle line:84%
>>SIMON: A little
bit of vulnerability.

00:38:19.550 --> 00:38:21.020 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Be a little bit naive.

00:38:21.020 --> 00:38:23.810 align:middle line:84%
Right now, we all want to feel
like we've got some control

00:38:23.810 --> 00:38:25.582 align:middle line:90%
over this out of control game.

00:38:25.582 --> 00:38:27.290 align:middle line:84%
>>SIMON: You want to
have a strong spine,

00:38:27.290 --> 00:38:28.750 align:middle line:90%
but an open heart.

00:38:28.750 --> 00:38:30.088 align:middle line:90%
And that's the key.

00:38:30.088 --> 00:38:31.880 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's a very
good way to put it.

00:38:31.880 --> 00:38:35.360 align:middle line:84%
OK, Simon, any final thoughts
on this for your own strategies

00:38:35.360 --> 00:38:36.230 align:middle line:90%
for this period?

00:38:36.230 --> 00:38:39.950 align:middle line:10%
Because we're in the outsider
period, first of all I'll say,

00:38:39.950 --> 00:38:42.248 align:middle line:10%
people need to go and take
a look at "Dharma Types."

00:38:42.248 --> 00:38:43.790 align:middle line:10%
We've done a couple
of shows on this.

00:38:43.790 --> 00:38:44.150 align:middle line:10%
>>SIMON: Yeah.

00:38:44.150 --> 00:38:46.490 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: "The 5 Dharma Types"
and how each one of those.

00:38:46.490 --> 00:38:47.948 align:middle line:84%
In one of our recent
interviews, we

00:38:47.948 --> 00:38:49.940 align:middle line:84%
talked about how each
one of these types

00:38:49.940 --> 00:38:51.540 align:middle line:84%
fits in with this
outsider phase.

00:38:51.540 --> 00:38:52.340 align:middle line:90%
>>SIMON: Yeah.

00:38:52.340 --> 00:38:54.350 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But in
general, for all people,

00:38:54.350 --> 00:38:58.160 align:middle line:84%
any kind of sage advice coming
from you as a practitioner

00:38:58.160 --> 00:38:59.810 align:middle line:90%
of many lovely things?

00:38:59.810 --> 00:39:01.957 align:middle line:84%
>>SIMON: Well, the first
is, always do your Dharma.

00:39:01.957 --> 00:39:03.290 align:middle line:90%
That's the answer to everything.

00:39:03.290 --> 00:39:04.830 align:middle line:90%
Do what you're supposed to do.

00:39:04.830 --> 00:39:07.940 align:middle line:10%
The second is, I wrote a book
called "The Dharma Method"

00:39:07.940 --> 00:39:10.230 align:middle line:10%
just recently, and
in that, I give

00:39:10.230 --> 00:39:12.330 align:middle line:10%
11 things you can do every day.

00:39:12.330 --> 00:39:13.130 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:39:13.130 --> 00:39:16.340 align:middle line:84%
>>SIMON: From when you
have your cup of water,

00:39:16.340 --> 00:39:19.370 align:middle line:84%
speaking a little mantra
into it, a little prayer

00:39:19.370 --> 00:39:20.210 align:middle line:90%
in any language.

00:39:20.210 --> 00:39:22.070 align:middle line:84%
Sanskrit, Latin,
English, Hebrew, it

00:39:22.070 --> 00:39:25.920 align:middle line:84%
doesn't matter, to
put some of that,

00:39:25.920 --> 00:39:28.640 align:middle line:84%
and then you put that into you
to reorganize the molecules

00:39:28.640 --> 00:39:31.430 align:middle line:84%
in the water so they
help to organize you.

00:39:31.430 --> 00:39:33.110 align:middle line:84%
Little things like
that are free.

00:39:33.110 --> 00:39:37.970 align:middle line:84%
To getting up with the sunrise,
to creating a sacred community

00:39:37.970 --> 00:39:41.350 align:middle line:90%
of people who will check you.

00:39:41.350 --> 00:39:43.860 align:middle line:84%
Who will check yourself
before you wreck yourself.

00:39:43.860 --> 00:39:46.040 align:middle line:90%
Who keep you balanced.

00:39:46.040 --> 00:39:51.080 align:middle line:84%
So my advice is, you don't
have to, if you don't want

00:39:51.080 --> 00:39:52.730 align:middle line:84%
to talk into your
water, if you feel

00:39:52.730 --> 00:39:54.233 align:middle line:90%
it feels weird, that's fine.

00:39:54.233 --> 00:39:55.400 align:middle line:90%
Practice some of the others.

00:39:55.400 --> 00:39:56.550 align:middle line:90%
Get up at sunrise.

00:39:56.550 --> 00:39:57.350 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Big one.

00:39:57.350 --> 00:39:58.040 align:middle line:90%
>>SIMON: Right, big one.

00:39:58.040 --> 00:39:58.980 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Looking into
the sun at sunrise.

00:39:58.980 --> 00:40:00.770 align:middle line:84%
>>SIMON: Get your
pineal gland balanced,

00:40:00.770 --> 00:40:03.710 align:middle line:84%
because these are the
master glands here.

00:40:03.710 --> 00:40:05.810 align:middle line:84%
And when you don't,
your hormones

00:40:05.810 --> 00:40:07.670 align:middle line:90%
are off for the rest of the day.

00:40:07.670 --> 00:40:09.255 align:middle line:84%
Of course you going
to feel crappy.

00:40:09.255 --> 00:40:10.880 align:middle line:84%
And it's going to be
harder to make it,

00:40:10.880 --> 00:40:14.460 align:middle line:90%
harder to be equanimous.

00:40:14.460 --> 00:40:16.460 align:middle line:84%
But when you wake up with
the sun, that's great.

00:40:16.460 --> 00:40:17.960 align:middle line:84%
OK, you can't wake
up with the sun.

00:40:17.960 --> 00:40:20.540 align:middle line:84%
Fine, there are other
things you can do.

00:40:20.540 --> 00:40:25.040 align:middle line:84%
Eating a certain sattvic
diet, which I call.

00:40:25.040 --> 00:40:27.410 align:middle line:90%
And sacred movement.

00:40:27.410 --> 00:40:29.600 align:middle line:90%
So incorporating, do something.

00:40:29.600 --> 00:40:31.370 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Do things
in a conscious manner.

00:40:31.370 --> 00:40:34.770 align:middle line:84%
>>SIMON: Do something to
bring balance to your life.

00:40:34.770 --> 00:40:36.770 align:middle line:10%
It doesn't even
matter what it is.

00:40:36.770 --> 00:40:39.290 align:middle line:10%
Just do something rather,
because people tend to go,

00:40:39.290 --> 00:40:41.510 align:middle line:10%
oh my God, it's too
much, I can't, there's

00:40:41.510 --> 00:40:44.870 align:middle line:10%
this conspiracy
and this, and Simon

00:40:44.870 --> 00:40:47.360 align:middle line:10%
says we're all going to
go bankrupt and this.

00:40:47.360 --> 00:40:48.690 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:40:48.690 --> 00:40:50.940 align:middle line:90%
Just do something each day.

00:40:50.940 --> 00:40:53.040 align:middle line:84%
Even use your
lucky times to plug

00:40:53.040 --> 00:40:55.350 align:middle line:84%
into the universe and the
universe will support you.

00:40:55.350 --> 00:40:58.530 align:middle line:84%
Because when you do your
Dharma, Dharma supports you.

00:40:58.530 --> 00:40:59.640 align:middle line:90%
That's the answer.

00:40:59.640 --> 00:41:02.610 align:middle line:84%
When you do Adharma, you
will pay the consequences

00:41:02.610 --> 00:41:03.480 align:middle line:90%
at some point.

00:41:03.480 --> 00:41:06.105 align:middle line:84%
Maybe not today, maybe not
tomorrow, but some point.

